J.C. Penney Co Inc said sales for thefive weeks ended April Four for its JCPenney stores and catalogwere off 1.3 pct to 1.12 billion dlrs from 1.13 billion a yearbefore, with same-store sales off 1.5 pct.    The company said total company sales were off 0.2 pct to1.25 billion dlrs from 1.26 billion dlrs.    Penney said sales for ther first nine weeks of its fiscalyear for its JCPenney stores and catalogs were up 1.3 pct to1.90 billion dlrs from 1.87 billion dlrs a year before, withsame-store sales up 1.2 pct.    Penney said year to date sales company-wide were up 2.3 pctto 2.14 billion dlrs from 2.09 billion dlrs, with same-storesales up 2.2 pct.    Penney said "Sales were in line with expectations in lightof the shift of Easter from March in 1986 to April this year.Sales continued strong for catalog operations and,geographically, ranged from very active in the East to weak inthe economically depressed Southwest. Reuter&#3;